The article is a proclamation by President Donald J. Trump declaring October 6, 2019, as German-American Day. It celebrates the contributions of German Americans to the United States throughout history. The article highlights notable German American figures such as General Friedrich von Steuben, Levi Strauss, Charles M. Schwab, and Hilla Rebay, who have made significant impacts in various fields. It also acknowledges the 30th anniversary of the fall of the Berlin Wall, emphasizing the dedication of the United States and Germany to the rule of law and human rights. The proclamation encourages Americans to celebrate German-American achievements and contributions through appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs.